{
  "texts": [
    "TPOT is an automated machine learning system that takes in features and labels and uses genetic programming to output the best model with cross-validated classification accuracy.",
    "By using TPOT, a comprehensive search is conducted over a wide range of machine learning models.",
    "Among the available AutoML frameworks [54] [55] [56], we chose to use TPOT by virtue of its rapid development time.",
    "We evaluate the models obtained via TPOT according to classification accuracy, i.e., the ratio between correctly classified trials and the total number of trials in the validation set.",
    "Since the TUAR dataset we use in this paper is imbalanced, we also consider the F1 score."
  ]
}